*Setting up Mosek:
Download Mosek (http://www.mosek.com/index.php?id=7) and follow its installation manual 
(http://www.mosek.com/fileadmin/products/6_0/tools/doc/html/toolsinstall/index.html) to
install Mosek then add the Mosek's path to the environment. 

Here's an example for the tcsh shell:

setenv LD_LIBRARY_PATH /v/filer4b/v16q001/users/hntuyen/softwares/mosek/5/tools/platform/linux32x86/bin:$LD_LIBRARY_PATH
setenv PATH {$PATH}:/v/filer4b/v16q001/users/hntuyen/softwares/mosek/5/tools/platform/linux32x86/bin

* To learn weight using the max-margin method use the following command:

ut-learnwts-mm  -d -dC 1000 -infer "-ilp -ilpLPRelax" -lossAugmented

An example on the voting dataset:
ut-learnwts-mm -i voting.mln -t voting-train.db -o voting-learnwts-mm.mln -ne Democrat -d -dC 1000 -lossAugmented -infer "-ilp -ilpLPRelax"

To use the L1 version of the max-margin, add the flag -useL1.

* To get the prediction you can either use:
-exact MPE inference:
infer -ilp -ilpSolver 2

or
-approximation MPE inference based on LP-relaxation:
infer -ilp -ilpLPRelax
 